COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x130
STRING: I wondered how many times it had been this month.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x13c
STRING: I was heading to the practice room where Fal would be
waiting.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x148
STRING: She had her own schedule and things to do, so it wasn't
overly frequent.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x15e
STRING: But, we had been spending quite a lot of time together.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x172
STRING: I knocked on the door gently before entering, though it
probably wouldn't have been heard from within.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1a8
STRING: [Chris] “Hi, Fal.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1d2
STRING: When I greeted her, she was singing the same song she
always sings.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1fa
STRING: [Fal] “Oh, hi Chris.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x212
STRING: Perhaps she had become more comfortable with me, as
she didn't move her eyes from her score when she
spoke.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x228
STRING: I was always happy when she politely turned away from
what she was doing to say hello, but this kind of casual
interaction wasn't bad either.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x272
STRING: By the time she finished singing the last part of her
song, I had already prepared everything I needed and
was sitting at my Fortelle.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x288
STRING: She didn't need any more warming up, so we could
start any time we wanted.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x2c2
STRING: [Fal] “Shall we just rehearse for now?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x2d8
STRING: [Chris] “Sure.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x2ee
STRING: I responded, and briefly played a few notes.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x302
STRING: [Fal] “Okay then.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x330
STRING: Hmm...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x33c
STRING: [Chris] “Huh...?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x366
STRING: There was something just right about the atmosphere
in the practice room, and it caused a brief moment of
déjà vu.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x372
STRING: Had I experienced this before?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x37e
STRING: Obviously, it had not been with Fal.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x38a
STRING: The smell of a slightly moldy music room.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x396
STRING: A room with air so compressed, it seemed to press
against your eardrums.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x3a2
STRING: I suddenly remembered the unique atmosphere of the
music class that I had studied at as a child.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x3fa
STRING: We could always hear the sound of someone playing
the piano, or the voice of someone singing.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x412
STRING: Even if someone entered the room, the music would
never stop, and the room was always filled with the
sound of melodies.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x42a
STRING: And, before I knew it, I, too, had become a part of the
ensemble.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x468
STRING: I returned from my reminiscences, and quickly turned
my eyes towards Fal. Torta wouldn't have cared, but I
wasn't sure if it had bothered Fal or not.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4a4
STRING: She said nothing, and simply smiled.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4b0
STRING: I strongly doubted she had shared my moment of
nostalgia, but she didn't seem angry, nor troubled by it.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4e2
STRING: [Fal] “So, shall we begin?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4f8
STRING: I said nothing, and simply began to play.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x592
STRING: [Fal] “Yes, that was good.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5a8
STRING: Fal seemed quite satisfied, praising me before the
lingering sounds of the last notes faded.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5be
STRING: I was also pleased with our performance, and was able
to answer without feeling the need for modesty.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5d4
STRING: [Chris] “It was, wasn't it?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x606
STRING: [Fal] “I can't say it was perfect...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x634
STRING: But for the time being,
I think it's something we can be proud of.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x64a
STRING: The way she said this happily had spread to me, too,
and I also felt happy.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x660
STRING: And at the same time, I felt a tiny sense of pressure.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6b0
STRING: [Fal] “Phew... Good job.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6c6
STRING: [Chris] “You too!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6dc
STRING: After practicing numerous times, I was definitely getting
used to the song itself.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6e8
STRING: However, I was definitely not at a level that was
satisfactory.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6f4
STRING: Just looking at Fal who practiced so diligently, made
that painstakingly clear.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x70a
STRING: Of course it was her own original song, so she had
already practiced it a lot, but even taking that into
consideration, her voice was still amazing.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x72a
STRING: We were on different levels.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x752
STRING: [Fal] “What's wrong?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x768
STRING: [Chris] “Nothing, just... I was thinking I've still got a long
way to go.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x786
STRING: [Fal] “You mean, about the song we just performed?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x79c
STRING: [Chris] “Yeah... I guess.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x7ce
STRING: [Fal] “Well, it's only our third time, right?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x7fc
STRING: I suppose we don't have that much more time, but it's
not like we're pressed badly for time, either.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x812
STRING: [Chris] “But...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x828
STRING: That was the problem.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x834
STRING: We definitely were running out of time.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x840
STRING: Would it be best if I chose her as my partner...?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x84c
STRING: Arie was under the impression I would partner up with
Torta, and thus had no suspicions of me.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x858
STRING: I felt like that in itself may be a betrayal towards Arie,
so I had decided to find someone else.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x86e
STRING: But if the result of that decision was also a betrayal...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x896
STRING: [Fal] “Chris...?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x8ac
STRING: [Chris] “Huh?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x8ca
STRING: [Fal] “Is everything okay? You seem to have a lot on
your mind today.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x8e0
STRING: [Chris] “Yeah, everything is fine... Sorry, this just seems
to be a bad habit of mine. My best friends say I do it a
lot. I didn't mean to ignore you or make you feel
uncomfortable.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x926
STRING: [Fal] “It's okay, I'm not bothered at all. But, if there is
something on your mind, you can talk to me about it if
you like.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x946
STRING: [Chris] “No, really it's...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x978
STRING: [Fal] “There's no need to hold back. After all, we are...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x98e
STRING: [Chris] “We are...?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9a4
STRING: We weren't partners.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9b0
STRING: We were practicing together based on that agreement.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9bc
STRING: As potential partners... As a replacement for someone
else.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9c8
STRING: But we were reaching the point where it was becoming
hard to keep saying that.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9de
STRING: Was it okay to continue with this ambiguous
relationship of ours?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9ea
STRING: In the end it might result in a burden not only for me,
but Fal also.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa1c
STRING: [Fal] “Hm?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa4a
STRING: We're friends, aren't we?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa56
STRING: [Chris] “Yeah... Yeah, we are.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa88
STRING: [Fal] “Of course, we are both potential music partners,
too.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xab6
STRING: But, if for some reason it doesn't work out, there's
no reason for us to not be friends, I guess.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xad6
STRING: [Chris] “Friends, huh...?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb08
STRING: [Fal] “Or, is that being a little presumptuous since we
only just met?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb28
STRING: [Chris] “No, of course not! I mean, I'm happy that you
think of me as a friend.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb64
STRING: [Fal] “Hehe, thanks.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb7a
STRING: Almost as if she was able to see into my heart, she
brought up the very topic I had been concerned about.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb90
STRING: I felt some of the weight had been removed from my
shoulders, but I was still undecided about whether I
should tell her about Arie.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xba6
STRING: “I have a girlfriend, so we can't be partners.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xbb2
STRING: But, that might have sounded a bit too self-conscious.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xbbe
STRING: I wondered if I was still just stuck on what Torta had
told me about music partners, and how they often
ended up in a romantic relationship.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xbfa
STRING: [Fal] “Your friends are right about your bad habit.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc10
STRING: [Chris] “Yeah...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc42
STRING: [Fal] “Aha-ha, I'll remember it.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc70
STRING: So, what shall we do?
Practice, practice, practice, for now?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc86
STRING: [Chris] “I guess so. We don't have that much time left.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xca4
STRING: [Fal] “That's right.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xcd2
STRING: Uh... That just made me think, it's
fine for me either way as my song won't change... But if
you choose to go with a different partner, your song
will change too, right?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xcf2
STRING: [Chris] “Yeah, that's right. But, I practice other songs in
my morning lessons, and it's not like I practice with a
whole bunch of other people.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd38
STRING: [Fal] “I see... But, we're going to have to make a
decision eventually.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd4e
STRING: [Chris] “Yeah... That's true.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd80
STRING: [Fal] “Aha-ha.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xdae
STRING: I'm sorry, that sounded like I was trying to
coerce you. Take your time to decide.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xdc4
STRING: [Chris] “Thanks... I will.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xdf6
STRING: [Fal] “Shall we continue practicing, then?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe0c
STRING: [Chris] “Alright.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe24
STRING: And then the practice room was filled with music.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xea6
STRING: [Fal] “Alright, I'll see you next time.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xebc
STRING: [Chris] “Oh? You've got plans today?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xeee
STRING: [Fal] “Yes. I'm a little busy today, so I won't be able to
leave with you.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf0e
STRING: [Chris] “Is it actually possible for you to be any busier...?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf24
STRING: A part-time job, music practice and... Just thinking
about it made my head spin.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf56
STRING: [Fal] “I suppose it is. But, I'm busy mostly by choice.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf6c
STRING: [Chris] “Yeah, but even so...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf9e
STRING: [Fal] “Anyway, I really have to get going. See you next
time!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfb4
STRING: [Chris] “Oh, right. See you.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfd6
STRING: It was an innocently made promise to meet again.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfe2
STRING: Which of course had no deeper meaning than that.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfee
STRING: Among friends, it was a very normal thing.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xffa
STRING: The fact that it had become natural and innocent like
that, was perhaps what I was surprised at.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1010
STRING: I guess it was just as she had put it, that we were
simply friends.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1026
STRING: Even if we did not partner up in the end, would she still
think of me as a friend?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1046
STRING: It was then that I realized it was pointless to think that
much about it.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1052
STRING: There was no way to know what life would be like after
graduating.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1068
STRING: For some reason or another, I may never see Fal again.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x107e
STRING: For example, if I end up being partners with Torta or
something.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x108a
STRING: And of course, Lise was another possibility.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1096
STRING: If that happened, would Fal still smile and think of me
as a friend?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x10ac
STRING: Thinking about these things, I watched her walk in a
slight hurry down the hallway of the Second Hall.
